LOCAL COVER WITH RED "HAMILTON/+BERMUDA+" C.D.S. OF 1st-TYPE "PEROT" STAMPS FAME; 2 Sept. 1850 small env. simply addressed to "William A Atwood Esq." who was a J.P. and Assembly Member based at Port Royal, with a very fine bright red PM4 "HAMILTON/+BERMUDA+" c.d.s. on the front; this is a contemporary strike of the mark with which Perot made his famous Postmaster's Provisionals stamps. The 1d local rate had to be prepaid but was 
