1029  	 	LOCAL COVER WITH RED "HAMILTON/+BERMUDA+" C.D.S. OF 1st-TYPE "PEROT" STAMPS FAME; 2(?) Oct. 1850 small mourning env. (small corner fault but attractive) addressed to "Miss Till, St. Georges" with a mostly very fine bright red PM4 "HAMILTON/+BERMUDA+" c.d.s. (small worm-hole adjacent but barely visible) on the front; this is a contemporary strike of the mark with which Perot made his famous Postmaster's Provisionals stamps. The 1d local rate had to be prepaid but was seldom actually marked on letters at this date; there was a daily post between Hamilton & St. Georges. Attractive. PHOTO.  	£120
